Though slightly verbose and not usual for C#, that did work. Here's what I came up with, in case anyone else tries this:

``` C#
public abstract class Result<T>
{
    internal Result() { }
}

public sealed class Success<T> : Result<T>
{
    public T Result { get; set; }
}

public sealed class Failure<T> : Result<T>
{
    public string Message { get; set; }
}

public static class Result
{
    public static string GetValue<T>(this Result<T> res) => res match (
        case Success<T> succ : (Object)succ.Result match (
            case string s : s
            case int i : i.ToString("N")
            case var x : x.ToString()
        )

        case Failure<T> f : $"Error: {f.Message}"
    );

    public static Result<R> Map<T, R>(this Result<T> r, Func<T, R> transform) => r match (
        case Success<T> s : Success.From(transform(s.Result))
        case Failure<T> f : Failure.From<R>(f.Message)
    );
}
```

Signature for `map` is a bloody ripper, but at least the actual implementation is quite simple.

